name: PyFMI-2.9.8
body:
* Resolved a bug in the example fmi20_bouncing_ball_native where a step-event is triggered in every timestep.
* Changed some imports to remove DeprecationWarnings.

name: PyFMI-2.9.7
body:
* Added an argument to ResultDymolaBinary to allow for reading updated data from the loaded file.
* Added option "synchronize_simulation" to allow for synchronizing simulation with (scaled) real-time.

name: PyFMI-2.9.6
body:
--- PyFMI-2.9.6 ---
    * Added setup.cfg that lists all Python package dependencies in order to run PyFMI.
    * Resolved an issue that would occur when reading large result files or streams causing the data to be corrupt due to an integer overflow.

name: PyFMI-2.9.5
body: Updated structure for diagnostic variables and leading prefix has been changed as well. Removed check for name clash between model variables and diagnostic variables.

name: PyFMI-2.9.4
body: Updated tests that should've been updated in earlier releases. Compared to the earlier release 2.9.3, there are no changes to the functionality of PyFMI for this release.

name: PyFMI-2.9.3
body: PyFMI 2.9.3 contains a minor addition with an additional class variable in one of the result IO classes to keep track of the file position of the data header.

name: PyFMI-2.9.2
body: Made error check with 'dynamic_diagnostics' less restrictive to also allow custom result handlers. In 2.9.1 only a binary result handler was allowed.

name: PyFMI-2.9.1
body:
--- PyFMI-2.9.1 ---
    * Added new simulation option 'dynamic_diagnostics' to better illustrate the purpose of enabling 'logging' when 'result_handling' is set to True.
    * Updated also such that the text file 'model identifier + _debug.txt' is no longer generated when logging to the binary result file.

name: PyFMI-2.9
body:
Released PyFMI 2.9

1. Saving diagnostic data in binary result file instead of log file.
3. Attempts to get continuous states when there are no such states will now return fmi2_status_ok instead of an error.

name: PyFMI-2.8.9
body: This release contains a revert of a change initially added in 2.8.8. It was reverted due to need of further consideration before the implementation can be finalized.
